  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypothesis: In giant cell arteritis (GCA), a short initial treatment with anti-TNF may allow
      a faster decrease of steroids dosage and therefore avoid some of the adverse events of
      steroids.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The protocol consists of a SC injection of adalimumab or placebo every 2 weeks for 10 weeks
      added to steroids
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
